Deploying production sync — do not run


What PAUSE_SYNC is:
It's just a file. A regular file named PAUSE_SYNC (no extension) sitting in the root of the glasshouse-data repo on the main branch.
The script checks at startup: "Does a file named PAUSE_SYNC exist in the working directory?"

If yes → script exits immediately, does nothing
If no → script runs normally

That's the entire mechanism. It's a kill switch you can flip without editing any code.

What goes in the file:
Literally anything. The file's contents don't matter — only its existence. The script only checks "is this file here?" — it doesn't read what's inside.
You could put:

A single space
The word "paused"
A timestamp
Nothing at all (empty file)
